## 🔍 5. Debugging using echo

```bash
echo "Checking memory..."
```

👉 Helps track script execution

---

## 🐍 6. grep Command

```bash
grep "error" file.txt
```

👉 Filters specific data from output

---

## 🔄 7. Pipe (|) Operator

```bash
command1 | command2
```

👉 Output of command1 → input of command2

Example:

```bash
ps -ef | grep nginx
```

---

## 🔀 8. Combining ps + grep

```bash
ps -ef | grep process_name
```

👉 Used to find running processes

---

## ⚠️ 9. Pipe Limitation

* Pipe works with STDOUT → STDIN
* Some commands like `date` behave differently

---

## 📊 10. awk Command

```bash
ps -ef | awk '{print $1}'
```

👉 Extracts specific columns

---

## 🛑 11. Error Handling (VERY IMPORTANT)

### Exit on error

```bash
set -e
```

### Fail if pipe fails

```bash
set -o pipefail
```

---

## 🌐 12. curl Command

```bash
curl https://example.com
```

👉 Used to fetch data from APIs/web

### Example:

```bash
curl url | grep error
```

---

## ⬇️ 13. wget Command

```bash
